### useDeferredValue

`useDeferredValue` lets you defer updating a non-urgent part of the UI. It accepts a value and returns a deferred copy that may lag behind the original during urgent updates.

---

### Syntax

```jsx
import { useDeferredValue } from 'react';

const deferredValue = useDeferredValue(value);
```

### Example: Search with Filtering

```jsx
function SearchPage({ query }) {
  const deferredQuery = useDeferredValue(query);
  const isStale = query !== deferredQuery;

  const results = useMemo(() => {
    return filterItems(items, deferredQuery);
  }, [items, deferredQuery]);

  return (
    <>
      <input value={query} onChange={...} />
      <List style={{ opacity: isStale ? 0.5 : 1 }}>
        {results.map(item => <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>)}
      </List>
    </>
  );
}
```

### How It Works

| Aspect | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| Urgent update | Input stays responsive immediately |
| Deferred update | List re-renders after urgent work finishes |
| Stale state | `isStale` flag for visual feedback |
| Dependency | Works alongside useMemo for expensive computations |

### Comparison with useTransition

| Hook | Use Case |
|------|----------|
| `useDeferredValue` | Deferring a value you receive (props) |
| `useTransition` | Deferring state updates you trigger |

> **Key Point:** useDeferredValue helps keep inputs responsive when rendering expensive lists. Combine with useMemo to avoid recomputing during urgent renders. Show visual feedback using the isStale flag.

codeExample:
import { useDeferredValue, useMemo } from 'react';

function ProductList({ products, filter }) {
  const deferredFilter = useDeferredValue(filter);

  const filtered = useMemo(() => {
    return products.filter(p =>
      p.name.toLowerCase().includes(deferredFilter.toLowerCase())
    );
  }, [products, deferredFilter]);

  return (
    <ul style={{ opacity: filter !== deferredFilter ? 0.5 : 1 }}>
      {filtered.map(p => <li key={p.id}>{p.name}</li>)}
    </ul>
  );
}
